## âš™ï¸ KP Embedded Syntax

### ğŸ”Œ GPIO
```kp
pin_mode(5, "OUTPUT")
pin_mode(6, "INPUT")

digital_write(5, 1)  # HIGH
digital_write(5, 0)  # LOW

val = digital_read(6)
print("Pin 6 state:", val)
```

### âš¡ PWM
```kp
pwm_start(3, freq=1000, duty=50)
pwm_set_duty(3, 75)
pwm_stop(3)
```

### ğŸ”— I2C
```kp
i2c_setup()
i2c_write(addr=0x76, reg=0xF4, data=0x27)
val = i2c_read(addr=0x76, reg=0xF4, len=1)
print("Register val:", val)
```

### ğŸ§¬ SPI
```kp
spi_setup()
spi_write([0xAA, 0xBB, 0xCC])
data = spi_read(3)
print("SPI data:", data)
```

### ğŸ“¡ UART (Serial)
```kp
uart_setup(baud=9600)
uart_send("Hello KP")
msg = uart_receive()
print("Received:", msg)
```

### ğŸš ADC (Analog Read)
```kp
value = analog_read(0)
print("Analog value:", value)
```

